Package: punycode
Type: Package
Title: Encode, Decode and Validate International Domain Names
Version: 0.2.2
Date: 2015-06-05
Author: Bob Rudis <bob@rudis.net> [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Bob Rudis <bob@rudis.net>
Description: A toolkit for encoding, decoding and validating international
             domain names (IDNA or Punycode formats). In order to build and
             install this package from source, the GNU IDN Library must be
             present on the system and is available as a package on most
             Linux distributions and installs cleanly on OS X and Windows.
URL: http://github.com/hrbrmstr/punycode
     http://www.gnu.org/software/libidn/
BugReports: https://github.com/hrbrmstr/punycode/issues
License: GPL-2
Suggests:
    testthat,
    knitr
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0.0),
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 0.11.2),
    stringr
VignetteBuilder: knitr
NeedsCompilation: yes
Type: Package
SystemRequirements: libidn
LinkingTo: Rcpp
